NOT JUST BEARDS.

00:02:23.780 --> 00:02:28.280
Scientists from the University of Arizona
tested the hairbrushes of 30 different women,

00:02:28.280 --> 00:02:35.069
and found 20 percent more bacteria living
on the brush than on the bathroom sink[8].

00:02:35.069 --> 00:02:39.240
The brushes contained dead skin, oil and (obviously)
hair!

00:02:39.240 --> 00:02:44.629
Okay, okay, I'll stop fear-mongering; remember,
the flora which live in and on our bodies

00:02:44.629 --> 00:02:47.750
ISN'T going to harm us; it's symbiotic.

00:02:47.750 --> 00:02:50.100
It feeds on our oils and dead skin cells.

00:02:50.100 --> 00:02:56.130
the bacteria living in your beard is the same
that lives on your skin, and it's ALWAYS THERE.

00:02:56.130 --> 00:02:59.590
Shaving won't rid you of this evil beard bacteria.

00:02:59.590 --> 00:03:04.830
If, for some reason, you ARE worried; all
bacteria can be managed by regular hygiene:

00:03:04.830 --> 00:03:08.660
shampoo or soap your hair to cut oil and thus
bacterial load.

00:03:08.660 --> 00:03:14.260
Also, just a general non-gross rule, make
sure there's no FOOD caught in your beard!

